The Italian Foreign Minister, Franco Frattini, mentioned in Belgrade the role played by secret agents and members of the Italian special forces.
“We must recognize that we have achieved this result thanks to the professionalism and efficiency of our men from the secret services, the special forces,” he said without going into details.
He also denied the payment of a ransom.
The day before, the Sudanese army claimed to have intercepted during a patrol an off-road vehicle with the hijackers on board, killing six, including the Chadian leader and arresting two.
He also claimed that they were related to a Darfur rebel group, the Sudan-Unity Liberation Movement (SLA-U), a claim immediately denied by this group.
